The paper focuses on learning a navigation policy for a robot to actively search for an object of interest in an indoor environment solely from its visual inputs. This involves object recognition, deep reinforcement learning, and control policy learning, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
